I just wanted to throw in my 2 cents when it comes to Jewelcraft.  I have a level 34 Enchanter with a skill level of 238 in Jewelcraft.  The reason I don't think it is a good idea for non Enchanters to be Jewelers is you cannot compete on prices.  While I was raising my skill I flooded the Bazaar with the level I was working on.  My main goal was to raise my skill and if I made a little money that was great.  As a result I sold in large volumes at a low price.  These volumes allowed me to raise my skill and still cover the cost of my failures.  Anyone who paid even a low price for the enchanting would not be able to break even.  Another problem you will have, that will not become apparent until you are in deep, is that it is fairly easy to find someone to enchant silver, electrum, and even gold for a small cost or even free.  Once you get to platinum things change.  As a level 34 Enchanter there is no way I am going to spend 20 minutes enchanting platinum bricks unless you pay me great money.  I'll give you Clarity or any other buff I have for free, but these bricks are a whole diffrent story.  I hate taking the time to enchant them for myself.  People say mana is free, but for a pure caster, that is the biggest consumer of my time.  And in reality the only true thing of worth in the game is play time.  So that is my 2 cents.  There are many crafts out there.  Most seem to go hand in hand with diffrent classes.  It would be better to chose one that would be a better fit.  But if you insist that you know better, be my guest.  Just don't complain when your Enchanter buddy who used to enchant stuff for free is no longer playing the game as much.  And you find yourself paying 200PP to get a stack of platinum bars enchanted.

