Disclaimer - Yes, I know this post was pre-patch with shared bank and mass enchant spells but I'm refuting it anyway for other that start to think twice about doing this skill post-patch.

<i>The reason I don't think it is a good idea for non Enchanters to be Jewelers is you cannot compete on prices.</i>

Why would other classes not be able to "compete on prices"? Prices of what? Gold? Jewels?

I'm a jeweler and a druid.  My wisdom is 255 and with my "charisma gear" I can put my CHA over 130.  Prices stop lowering from NPC merchants once your Cha is 130+.
So I have that base covered.  You will not get a better price than me on that stuff.

<i>Anyone who paid even a low price for the enchanting would not be able to break even.</i>

Lets see.  I'm a druid, I want to be a jeweler but I don't want to pay for someone to enchant my gold...
*lightbulb* So I created an enchanter alt to do this for me.  With the new shared bank and level 49 "mass enchant spells" which enchant 5 peices of gold/silver/etc at a time ..it doesnt take long - Four casts enchants 1 stack.

Why am I bothering with jewelcraft? For quests like 8th shawl and basically just for fun.  Its not costing me any more than it would anyone else.

